candidates.stmt:
If elected onto Suffolk County Council I promise to:
1. Hold Suffolk Highways to account to prioritise addressing the terrible state of our roads, sort out potholes, improve & maintain better the road surface, review and improve road markings, and clean road signs;
2. Fight for increased and improved local SEND education provision especially at primary school age, as there is too limited number of places, leaving children barred from education. By improving this local provision this will save taxpayers's money by reducing the transport bill;
3. Improve the provision and support available from both adult & children social services; and
4. Improve local bus services in/around the town, to encourage use of local businesses and also reduce the number of cars in town, which may help with the ongoing parking issues.
